Srikumar K.S's jexpr is an experimental (and it seems abandoned) attempt at doing just this:<p><a href="http://srikumarks.github.com/jexpr/" rel="nofollow">http://srikumarks.github.com/jexpr/</a><p><pre><code>  {do: [
        {fetchURL: "http://some.data.source/",
          timeout: 30.0,
           onfail: {raiseError: "URL not reachable"}},
        {fork: [
            {displayInElement: "element_id"},
            {cacheInLocalStorage: "prefix"}
            ]}]}
</code></pre>
more here:<p><a href="http://srikumarks.github.com/gyan/2012/04/15/j-expressions/" rel="nofollow">http://srikumarks.github.com/gyan/2012/04/15/j-expressions/</a><p><a href="http://srikumarks.github.com/gyan/2012/04/14/creating-dsls-in-javascript-using-j-expressions/" rel="nofollow">http://srikumarks.github.com/gyan/2012/04/14/creating-dsls-i...</a>
